  <front>
   <head>THE IMMORTALITY OF VIRTUE. TO MRS. FRINSHAM.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">FROM these numbers as they flow,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Shepherd-maids this moral know;</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Soon shall Beauty's brightest bloom</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Moulder in the cheerless tomb;</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Charms that light the blaze of love,</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Soon the force of time shall prove;</l>
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Vainly beams the glist'ning eye,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Quench'd in dust each star shall lie;</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Yet when Death's destructive dart</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Chills to rest the beating heart,</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Virtue's flame unquench'd shall burn,</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+-" line_length="8">Cheer the grave, and gild the urn.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
